  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375\u000368F.",
    "Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish and set aside.",
    "In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, cayenne pepper, ground cardamom, ground cumin, ground coriander, ground cayenne, ground fennel, ground anise, and ground fenugreek.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs, vanilla extract, and salt.",
    "Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix until just combined.",
    "Fold in the grated coconut, unsalted butter, and chopped nuts.",
    "Pour the mixture into the prepared baking dish and smooth the top.",
    "Bake for 35 minutes, or until the edges are golden brown and the center is set.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for 5 minutes before slicing and serving.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with additional chopped nuts if desired.",
    "Note: If desired, you can also make this recipe in a 9x9 inch baking dish. Simply adjust the baking time as needed.",
